          </div>
          <div class="degree-card">
            <h3>DBA (Doctor of Business Administration)</h3>
            <p>Professional doctorate for business leaders. Common in corporate and consulting roles.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="degree-card">
            <h3>EdD (Doctor of Education)</h3>
            <p>Professional doctorate for education leaders. Required for senior school administration.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="degree-card">
            <h3>MD (Doctor of Medicine)</h3>
            <p>Medical doctorate. Subject to <a href="/specialized/medical/dha-dataflow/">DHA licensing requirements</a>.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <h2>DHA Requirements (Healthcare Professionals)</h2>

        <p>Healthcare professionals with doctoral degrees face the most rigorous verification. The Dubai Health Authority uses <a href="/specialized/medical/dha-dataflow/">DataFlow verification</a> to authenticate all credentials.</p>

        <h3>What DHA Requires</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Primary Source Verification:</strong> DataFlow contacts your university directly to verify your doctorate</li>
          <li><strong>Translation:</strong> <a href="/legal-translation-dubai/">MOJ-certified translation</a> of degree certificate</li>
          <li><strong>Transcripts:</strong> Full academic <a href="/personal/academic/transcripts/">transcript translation</a> showing doctoral coursework</li>
          <li><strong>Attestation:</strong> Home country attestation plus UAE MOFA</li>
        </ul>

        <div class="authority-box dha">
          <h4><i class="fas fa-hospital"></i> DHA Doctoral Requirements</h4>
          <ul>
            <li>DataFlow Primary Source Verification</li>
            <li>MOJ-certified Arabic translation</li>
            <li>Full attestation chain</li>
            <li>Transcript verification</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="timeline">Timeline: 4-8 weeks (DataFlow verification varies)</p>
        </div>

        <h2>MOHRE Requirements (Employment)</h2>

        <p>For private sector employment, the Ministry of Human Resources and Emiratisation (MOHRE) reviews your qualifications during work permit processing.</p>

        <h3>Standard Employment</h3>
        <p>Most private employers require:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><a href="/personal/academic/degree/">Degree certificate translation</a> (MOJ-certified)</li>
          <li>Full attestation chain (home country → UAE Embassy → MOFA)</li>
          <li><a href="/personal/academic/transcripts/">Transcript translation</a> (sometimes requested)</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Government Employment</h3>
        <p>Government positions and some semi-government entities also require:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><a href="/resources/mohesr-equivalency/">MOHESR equivalency certificate</a></li>
          <li>Additional verification steps</li>
        </ul>

        <div class="authority-box mohre">
          <h4><i class="fas fa-building"></i> MOHRE Doctoral Requirements</h4>
          <ul>
            <li>MOJ-certified Arabic translation</li>
            <li>Full attestation chain</li>
            <li>MOHESR equivalency (government roles only)</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="timeline">Timeline: 2-4 weeks (translation + attestation)</p>
        </div>

        <h2>MOHESR Equivalency Requirements</h2>

        <p>The Ministry of Higher Education and Scientific Research evaluates foreign degrees for UAE recognition. Not everyone needs equivalency—but certain situations require it.</p>

        <h3>When You Need MOHESR Equivalency</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><a href="/services/golden-visa-translation/">Golden Visa professional category</a> applications</li>
          <li>Government employment</li>
          <li>Academic positions at UAE universities</li>
          <li>Professional licensing in regulated fields</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>When Translation Alone Suffices</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Private sector employment (most cases)</li>
          <li>Internal company promotions</li>
          <li>Business visa applications</li>
        </ul>

        <p>Read our <a href="/resources/mohesr-equivalency/">complete MOHESR equivalency guide</a> to understand when you need this additional step.</p>

        <div class="authority-box mohesr">
          <h4><i class="fas fa-graduation-cap"></i> MOHESR Doctoral Requirements</h4>
          <ul>
            <li>Fully attested degree certificate</li>
            <li>MOJ-certified translation</li>
            <li>Official transcripts (attested + translated)</li>
            <li>Passport copy</li>
            <li>Application through MOHESR portal</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="timeline">Timeline: 2-3 weeks after submission</p>
        </div>

        <h2>Distance Education Doctorates</h2>

        <p>Online and distance doctoral programs face extra scrutiny in the UAE. If you earned your PhD or DBA through distance learning, verify recognition before relying on it for employment.</p>

        <h3>Accepted Distance Doctorates</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Degrees from universities with proper accreditation in their home country</li>
          <li>Programs with residency requirements (hybrid programs)</li>
          <li>Universities on the MOHESR recognized institution list</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Potentially Problematic</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Fully online programs from unaccredited institutions</li>
          <li>Degrees from "diploma mills"</li>
          <li>Programs not recognized by home country education ministry</li>
        </ul>

        <p>See our <a href="/resources/distance-education-uae/">distance education guide</a> for detailed information on which online degrees UAE authorities accept.</p>

        <h2>Translation Process for Doctoral Degrees</h2>

        <p>Doctoral certificates often contain specialized terminology. Proper translation requires understanding of:</p>

        <ul>
          <li>Academic titles and their Arabic equivalents</li>
          <li>Degree classification (cum laude, distinction, etc.)</li>
          <li>Field of study terminology</li>
          <li>Institutional naming conventions</li>
        </ul>

        <div class="tip-box">
          <h4><i class="fas fa-lightbulb"></i> What to Send for Translation</h4>
