            <li>Degree certificate (the main diploma)</li>
            <li>Transcript of records (if required by employer/authority)</li>
            <li>Degree supplement (if issued by European universities)</li>
            <li>Attestation stamps (we translate after attestation)</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

        <div class="faq-section">
          <details class="faq-item" name="faq">
            <summary>Do I need MOHESR equivalency for my PhD to work in UAE?</summary>
            <div class="faq-answer">
              <p>It depends on your employer. Government jobs and <a href="/services/golden-visa-translation/">Golden Visa professional category</a> require MOHESR equivalency. Private sector employers usually accept attested and translated documents without equivalency. Healthcare roles through DHA have their own verification through <a href="/specialized/medical/dha-dataflow/">DataFlow</a>.</p>
            </div>
          </details>

          <details class="faq-item" name="faq">
            <summary>How long does PhD translation take?</summary>
            <div class="faq-answer">
              <p>Translation alone takes 24-48 hours for most doctoral certificates. If you need <a href="/services/attestation/">attestation</a>, add 2-4 weeks depending on your home country. <a href="/resources/mohesr-equivalency/">MOHESR equivalency</a> adds another 2-3 weeks after attestation is complete.</p>
            </div>
          </details>

          <details class="faq-item" name="faq">
            <summary>Is a DBA treated the same as a PhD in UAE?</summary>
            <div class="faq-answer">
              <p>Yes. MOHRE and MOHESR treat Doctor of Business Administration (DBA) as equivalent to PhD. Both are doctoral-level qualifications. The same translation and attestation requirements apply to both degrees.</p>
            </div>
          </details>

          <details class="faq-item" name="faq">
            <summary>What if my PhD is from an online university?</summary>
            <div class="faq-answer">
              <p><a href="/resources/distance-education-uae/">Online doctoral degrees</a> face scrutiny. MOHRE may not accept degrees from unaccredited online institutions. Check if your university is on the MOHESR recognized list before applying for jobs requiring doctoral qualifications. Some distance PhDs from accredited universities are accepted with proper documentation.</p>
            </div>
          </details>

          <details class="faq-item" name="faq">
            <summary>Do I need to translate my PhD thesis?</summary>
            <div class="faq-answer">
              <p>Usually not. UAE authorities require translation of the <a href="/personal/academic/degree/">degree certificate</a> and <a href="/personal/academic/transcripts/">transcripts</a>, not the thesis itself. However, academic positions may request thesis abstracts. We translate what authorities actually require—typically the certificate and official transcripts.</p>
            </div>
          </details>
        </div>

        <h2>Next Steps</h2>

        <p>If you need your doctoral degree translated for UAE use:</p>

        <ol>
          <li><strong>Determine your purpose:</strong> Employment, Golden Visa, licensing?</li>
          <li><strong>Check equivalency needs:</strong> Does your situation require <a href="/resources/mohesr-equivalency/">MOHESR equivalency</a>?</li>
